3. The relative extinction values of HST\nand JWST near-IR bandpasses are predicted in 2.5% precision. As the observed\nreddening/extinction tracks are curved, the curvature correction needs to be\nconsidered when applying extinction correction.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Tue, 9 Apr 2019 10:12:35 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Wed, 24 Apr 2019 08:26:56 GMT"},{"version":"v3","created":"Mon, 15 Jul 2019 09:09:59 GMT"}],"update_date":"2019-07-16"}
